# 🛡️ Credit Card Fraud Detection System

A production-grade, end-to-end machine learning system for real-time credit card fraud detection — built with XGBoost, FastAPI, and a live dashboard.

---

## 📸 Overview

This project builds a complete fraud detection pipeline from raw data generation through to a live-scoring REST API and browser dashboard. It handles the real-world challenge of extreme class imbalance (~1.5% fraud rate) using SMOTE oversampling, Optuna hyperparameter tuning, and SHAP explainability.

---

## 🗂️ Project Structure

```
Credit-Card-Fraud-Detection/
├── generate_data.py          # Synthetic transaction generator (100K rows)
├── verify_setup.py           # Environment & dependency checker
├── main.py                   # Pipeline runner (--phase generate/ingest/all)
├── requirements.txt          # Python dependencies
├── .gitignore
│
├── data/                     # Generated at runtime (gitignored)
│   ├── transactions.csv
│   ├── transactions.parquet
│   ├── X_train / y_train / X_test / y_test (.parquet)
│   ├── feature_list.joblib
│   └── label_encoders.joblib
│
├── notebooks/
│   ├── 01_ingest.py          # Schema enforcement + type casting
│   ├── 02_eda.py             # 7 EDA charts → images/
│   ├── 03_features.py        # Feature engineering + SMOTE splits
│   ├── 04_train.py           # XGBoost + Optuna (50 trials) + evaluation
│   └── 05_explain.py         # SHAP waterfall, beeswarm, dependence plots
│
├── models/                   # Generated at runtime (gitignored)
│   ├── xgb_fraud_model.joblib
│   ├── optimal_threshold.joblib
│   ├── best_params.joblib
│   └── eval_metrics.joblib
│
├── images/                  # Charts generated at runtime (gitignored)
│
├── serving/
│   ├── api.py                # FastAPI app (4 endpoints)
│   └── test_api.py           # Endpoint test runner
│
└── apps/
    └── dashboard.html        # Live fraud scoring dashboard
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup

### 1. Clone & create virtual environment

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Neha-Joshi05/credit-card-fraud-detection.git
cd Credit-Card-Fraud-Detection

python -m venv venv
# Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate
# Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install pyarrow        # required for Parquet support
```

### 3. Verify your environment

```bash
python verify_setup.py
```

All items should show ✅ before proceeding.

---

## 🚀 Running the Pipeline

Run each phase in order:

```bash
# Phase 1 — Generate & ingest data
python generate_data.py
python notebooks/01_ingest.py

# Phase 2 — EDA & feature engineering
python notebooks/02_eda.py
python notebooks/03_features.py

# Phase 3 — Train model & explain
python notebooks/04_train.py       # ~3–5 min (50 Optuna trials)
python notebooks/05_explain.py

# Phase 4 — Serve API
uvicorn serving.api:app --reload --port 8000
```

Or run Phase 1 all at once:

```bash
python main.py --phase all
```

---

## 📊 Dataset

Synthetic dataset of **100,000 credit card transactions** generated with realistic fraud patterns:

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Total rows | 100,000 |
| Fraud rate | ~1.5% (1,500 fraud transactions) |
| Date range | 90-day window |
| Features | 19 raw → 25 engineered |

**Key features:** transaction amount, merchant category, country, device type, channel, velocity metrics (1h / 24h), time-of-day, international flag.

**Fraud patterns baked in:** night-time transactions, burst velocity, high-risk countries (NG, RU, XX), luxury/electronics merchants, international transactions.

---

## 🤖 Model

| Component | Detail |
|---|---|
| Algorithm | XGBoost (`XGBClassifier`) |
| Tuning | Optuna TPE sampler, 50 trials |
| Objective | Maximise PR-AUC (better than ROC-AUC for imbalanced data) |
| Imbalance handling | SMOTE (20% synthetic minority oversampling) |
| Split strategy | Time-aware (last 20% by timestamp = test set, no leakage) |
| Threshold | Optimal F1 threshold (tuned post-training) |

### Typical Metrics

| Metric | Score |
|---|---|
| ROC-AUC | ~0.97+ |
| PR-AUC | ~0.85+ |
| F1 Score | ~0.80+ |
| Precision | ~0.82+ |
| Recall | ~0.78+ |

*Metrics vary slightly per run due to stochastic data generation.*

---

## 🔍 Explainability

SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) charts are generated for the trained model:

- **Beeswarm plot** — global feature impact across all predictions
- **Bar chart** — mean |SHAP| feature importance ranking
- **Dependence plots** — top 4 features vs their SHAP values
- **Waterfall plots** — individual prediction breakdowns (highest-confidence fraud + borderline legit)

Charts saved to `images/14_shap_*.png`.

---

## 🌐 API

Start the API:

```bash
uvicorn serving.api:app --reload --port 8000
```

### Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/` | Health check + model status |
| `GET` | `/metrics` | Model performance metrics |
| `POST` | `/predict` | Score a single transaction |
| `POST` | `/predict/batch` | Score up to 1,000 transactions |

### Interactive Docs

- Swagger UI → [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)
- ReDoc → [http://localhost:8000/redoc](http://localhost:8000/redoc)

### Example Request

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/predict \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "amount": 48000,
    "merchant_cat": "luxury",
    "country": "NG",
    "city": "Unknown",
    "device_type": "mobile",
    "channel": "online",
    "hour": 3,
    "dayofweek": 6,
    "prev_24h_tx_count_card": 14,
    "prev_24h_amt_card": 72000,
    "prev_1h_tx_count_card": 7,
    "velocity_amt_1h": 38000,
    "is_international": 1,
    "is_night": 1
  }'
```

### Example Response

```json
{
  "fraud_score": 0.9341,
  "is_fraud": true,
  "risk_level": "CRITICAL",
  "threshold_used": 0.312,
  "top_risk_factors": [
    "Night-time transaction",
    "International transaction",
    "High-risk merchant category",
    "High-risk country",
    "Burst transaction activity detected"
  ],
  "timestamp": "2024-03-15T03:22:11.042Z"
}
```

---

## 🖥️ Dashboard

Open `apps/dashboard.html` in your browser while the API is running.

Features:
- Live API connection status (auto-ping every 15s)
- One-click fraud / legit sample presets
- Animated fraud score meter (0→1)
- Plain-English risk factor explanations
- Live transaction feed with risk badges (LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH / CRITICAL)
- Session stats: fraud count, legit count, average score
- Score history bar chart (last 20 predictions)
- Model F1 and ROC-AUC pulled live from API

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Data | pandas, numpy, pyarrow |
| ML | XGBoost, scikit-learn, imbalanced-learn |
| Tuning | Optuna (TPE sampler) |
| Explainability | SHAP |
| Visualisation | matplotlib, seaborn |
| API | FastAPI, uvicorn, pydantic |
| Persistence | joblib |
| Dashboard | Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS |

